This paper discusses the game-theoretic analysis of natural language communication, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the role of common sense and common belief, which are important topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the feasibility of game-theoretic account of language, which can be related to information theory (cs.IT) and social networks (cs.SI).
